Package: midiplayer
Version: 0.1.0
Section: sound
Priority: optional
Architecture: all
Depends: python3 (>= 3.10), python3-gi, python3-gi-cairo, gir1.2-gtk-4.0, fluidsynth, libfluidsynth3, fluid-soundfont-gm
Recommends: python3-pip
Maintainer: Pashkovsky Alexei <pulpoff@users.noreply.github.com>
Homepage: https://github.com/pulpoff/midiplayer
Description: Modern GTK4 MIDI sheet music player for Linux
 A MIDI file player that displays sheet music notation with a piano
 keyboard, real-time note highlighting, and FluidSynth-based audio
 synthesis. Based on MidiSheetMusic 2.6 by Madhav Vaidyanathan,
 ported to Python / GTK4 / Cairo / FluidSynth.
 .
 Features:
  - Sheet music engraving with treble/bass clef, key signatures,
    beamed notes, accidentals, rests, and measure bars
  - Piano keyboard with left-hand / right-hand highlighting
  - FluidSynth audio via PipeWire / PulseAudio / ALSA
  - Speed and volume controls with timeline scrubbing
  - Horizontal scrolling score with smooth auto-scroll during playback
